rlCdp.name: rlCdp

revisions.description: Added rlCdpSecondaryCacheTable. Added maxNeighborsExceededInSecondaryCache. Renamed maxNeighborsExceeded to maxNeighborsExceededInMainCache.
Added rlCdpGlobalLogMismatchDuplexEnable. Added rlCdpGlobalLogMismatchVoiceVlanEnable. Added rlCdpGlobalLogMismatchNativeVlanEnable.
Added rlCdpLogMismatchDuplexTrap. Added rlCdpLogMismatchVoiceVlanTrap. Added rlCdpLogMismatchNativeVlanTrap.

rlCdp.contactinfo: Postal: 170 West Tasman Drive San Jose , CA 95134-1706 USA Website: Cisco Small Business Support Community <http://www.cisco.com/go/smallbizsupport>
rlCdp.description: The private MIB module definition for CDP protocol.

RlCdpVersionTypes.name: RlCdpVersionTypes
RlCdpVersionTypes.description: version-v1 - cdp version 1 version-v2 - cdp version 2

RlCdpCounterTypes.name: RlCdpCounterTypes
RlCdpCounterTypes.description: v1OutputPackets counter specifies the number of sent CDP packets with version 1 v2OutputPackets counter specifies the number of sent CDP packets with version 2 v1InputPackets counter specifies the number of received CDP packets with version 1 v2InputPackets counter specifies the number of received CDP packets with version 2 totalInputPackets counter specifies the total number of received CDP packets totalOutputPackets counter specifies the total number of sent CDP packets illegalChksum counter specifies the number of received CDP packets with illegal checksum. errorPackets counter specifies the number of received CDP packets with other error (duplicated TLVs, illegal TLVs, etc.) maxNeighborsExceededInMainCache counter specifies the number of times a CDP neighbor could not be stored in the main cache. maxNeighborsExceededInSecondaryCache specifies counter the number of times a CDP neighbor could not be stored in the secondary cache.

RlCdpPduActionTypes.name: RlCdpPduActionTypes
RlCdpPduActionTypes.description: filtering - CDP packets would filtered (dropped). bridging - CDP packets bridged as regular data packets

rlCdpVersionAdvertised.name: rlCdpVersionAdvertised
rlCdpVersionAdvertised.description: Specifies the verison of sent CDP packets

rlCdpSourceInterface.name: rlCdpSourceInterface
rlCdpSourceInterface.description: Specifices the CDP source-interface, which the IP address advertised into TLV is accoding to this source-interface instead of the outgoing interface. value of 0 indicates no source interface. value must belong to an ethernet port/lag

rlCdpLogMismatchDuplexEnable.name: rlCdpLogMismatchDuplexEnable
rlCdpLogMismatchDuplexEnable.description: Enable logging messages when detecting mishmatch between advertised and received duplex mode. To enable loging on specific interface set the corresponing bit.

rlCdpCountersTable.name: rlCdpCountersTable
rlCdpCountersTable.description: This table contains all CDP counters values, indexed by counter name

rlCdpCountersEntry.name: rlCdpCountersEntry
rlCdpCountersEntry.description: The row definition for this table.

rlCdpCountersName.name: rlCdpCountersName
rlCdpCountersName.description: counter name used as key for counters table

rlCdpCountersValue.name: rlCdpCountersValue
rlCdpCountersValue.description: the value of the counter name specisifed by rlCdpCountersName, unsuppo will have no entry in the tab.

rlCdpCountersClear.name: rlCdpCountersClear
rlCdpCountersClear.description: By setting the MIB to True, all error and traffic counters are set to zero.

rlCdpCacheClear.name: rlCdpCacheClear
rlCdpCacheClear.description: By setting the MIB to True, all entries from the cdp cache table is deleted.

rlCdpVoiceVlanId.name: rlCdpVoiceVlanId
rlCdpVoiceVlanId.description: voice vlan Id, used as the Appliance Vlan-Id TLV

rlCdpCacheTable.name: rlCdpCacheTable
rlCdpCacheTable.description: The (conceptual) table contains externtion for the cdpCache table. indexed by cdpCacheEntry.

rlCdpCacheEntry.name: rlCdpCacheEntry
rlCdpCacheEntry.description: The row definition for this table.

rlCdpCacheVersionExt.name: rlCdpCacheVersionExt
rlCdpCacheVersionExt.description: This field contains the extention of the cdpCacheVersion field in the cdpCache table. In case the neighbour advertised the SW TLV as a string with length larger than 160, this field contains the chacters from place 160 and on. Zero-length strings indicates no Version field (TLV) was reported in the most recent CDP message, or it was smaller than 160 chars

rlCdpCacheTimeToLive.name: rlCdpCacheTimeToLive
rlCdpCacheTimeToLive.description: This field indicates the time remains in seconds till the entry should be expried.

rlCdpCacheCdpVersion.name: rlCdpCacheCdpVersion
rlCdpCacheCdpVersion.description: This field indicates the cdp version that was reported in the most recent CDP message.

rlCdpPduAction.name: rlCdpPduAction
rlCdpPduAction.description: Defines CDP packets handling when CDP is globally disabled.

rlCdpLogMismatchVoiceVlanEnable.name: rlCdpLogMismatchVoiceVlanEnable
rlCdpLogMismatchVoiceVlanEnable.description: Enable logging messages when detecting mishmatch between advertised and received voice VLAN. To enable logging on specific interface set the corresponing bit.

rlCdpLogMismatchNativeVlanEnable.name: rlCdpLogMismatchNativeVlanEnable
rlCdpLogMismatchNativeVlanEnable.description: Enable logging messages when detecting mishmatch between advertised and received native VLAN. To enable loging on specific interface set the corresponing bit.

rlCdpSecondaryCacheTable.name: rlCdpSecondaryCacheTable
rlCdpSecondaryCacheTable.description: The (conceptual) table contains partial information from cdpCache table. indexed by rlCdpSecondaryCacheEntry.

rlCdpSecondaryCacheEntry.name: rlCdpSecondaryCacheEntry
rlCdpSecondaryCacheEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the rlCdpSecondaryCacheTable, containing partial information received via CDP on one interface from one device. Entries appear when a CDP advertisement is received from a neighbor device. Entries disappear when CDP is disabled on the interface, globally or when the secondary cache is cleared

rlCdpSecondaryCacheMacAddress.name: rlCdpSecondaryCacheMacAddress
rlCdpSecondaryCacheMacAddress.description: The MAC address of the neighbor.

rlCdpSecondaryCachePlatform.name: rlCdpSecondaryCachePlatform
rlCdpSecondaryCachePlatform.description: The Device's Hardware Platform prefix, as reported in the most recent CDP message. The zero-length string indicates that no Platform field (TLV) was reported in the most recent CDP message.

rlCdpSecondaryCacheCapabilities.name: rlCdpSecondaryCacheCapabilities
rlCdpSecondaryCacheCapabilities.description: The Device's Functional Capabilities as reported in the most recent CDP message.

rlCdpSecondaryCacheVoiceVlanID.name: rlCdpSecondaryCacheVoiceVlanID
rlCdpSecondaryCacheVoiceVlanID.description: The remote device's VoIP VLAN ID, as reported in the most recent CDP message. This object is not instantiated if no Appliance VLAN-ID field (TLV) was reported in the most recently received CDP message.

rlCdpSecondaryCacheTimeToLive.name: rlCdpSecondaryCacheTimeToLive
rlCdpSecondaryCacheTimeToLive.description: This field indicates the number of seconds till the entry is expried.

rlCdpGlobalLogMismatchDuplexEnable.name: rlCdpGlobalLogMismatchDuplexEnable
rlCdpGlobalLogMismatchDuplexEnable.description: Globally enable/disable logging messages when detecting mishmatch between advertised and received duplex mode.

rlCdpGlobalLogMismatchVoiceVlanEnable.name: rlCdpGlobalLogMismatchVoiceVlanEnable
rlCdpGlobalLogMismatchVoiceVlanEnable.description: Globally enable/disable logging messages when detecting mishmatch between advertised and received voice VLAN.

rlCdpGlobalLogMismatchNativeVlanEnable.name: rlCdpGlobalLogMismatchNativeVlanEnable
rlCdpGlobalLogMismatchNativeVlanEnable.description: Globally enable/disable logging messages when detecting mishmatch between advertised and received native VLAN.

rlCdpTlvTable.name: rlCdpTlvTable
rlCdpTlvTable.description: The (conceptual) table contains the local advertised information. indexed by rlCdpTlvEntry.

rlCdpTlvEntry.name: rlCdpTlvEntry
rlCdpTlvEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the rlCdpTlvTable, containing local information advertised by CDP on one interface. Entries are available only when CDP is globally enabled, for interfaces on which CDP is enabled and the interface state is UP.

rlCdpTlvIfIndex.name: rlCdpTlvIfIndex
rlCdpTlvIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the local interface. A value of zero is used to access TLVs which do not changed between interfaces.

rlCdpTlvDeviceIdFormat.name: rlCdpTlvDeviceIdFormat
rlCdpTlvDeviceIdFormat.description: An indication of the format of Device-Id contained in the corresponding instance of rlCdpTlvDeviceId. serialNumber(1) indicates that the value of rlCdpTlvDeviceId object is in the form of an ASCII string contain the device serial number. macAddress(2) indicates that the value of rlCdpTlvDeviceId object is in the form of Layer 2 MAC address. other(3) indicates that the value of rlCdpTlvDeviceId object is in the form of a platform specific ASCII string contain info that identifies the device. For example: ASCII string contains serialNumber appended/prepened with system name.

rlCdpTlvDeviceId.name: rlCdpTlvDeviceId
rlCdpTlvDeviceId.description: The Device-ID string as will be advertised in subsequent CDP messages.

rlCdpTlvAddress1Type.name: rlCdpTlvAddress1Type
rlCdpTlvAddress1Type.description: The Inet address type of rlCdpTlvAddress1

rlCdpTlvAddress1.name: rlCdpTlvAddress1
rlCdpTlvAddress1.description: The (first) network-layer address of the device as will be advertised in the Address TLV of subsequent CDP messages. For example, if the corresponding instance of rlCdpTlvAddress1Type had the value 'ipv4(1)', then this object would be an IPv4-address.

rlCdpTlvAddress2Type.name: rlCdpTlvAddress2Type
rlCdpTlvAddress2Type.description: The Inet address type of rlCdpTlvAddress2

rlCdpTlvAddress2.name: rlCdpTlvAddress2
rlCdpTlvAddress2.description: The (first) network-layer address of the device as will be advertised in the Address TLV of subsequent CDP messages. For example, if the corresponding instance of rlCdpTlvAddress2Type had the value 'ipv6(2)', then this object would be an IPv6-address.

rlCdpTlvAddress3Type.name: rlCdpTlvAddress3Type
rlCdpTlvAddress3Type.description: The Inet address type of rlCdpTlvAddress3

rlCdpTlvAddress3.name: rlCdpTlvAddress3
rlCdpTlvAddress3.description: The (first) network-layer address of the device as will be advertised in the Address TLV of subsequent CDP messages. For example, if the corresponding instance of rlCdpTlvAddress3Type had the value 'ipv6(2)', then this object would be an IPv6-address.

rlCdpTlvPortId.name: rlCdpTlvPortId
rlCdpTlvPortId.description: The Port-ID string as will be advertised in subsequent CDP messages from this interface. This will typically be the value of the ifName object (e.g., 'Ethernet0').

rlCdpTlvCapabilities.name: rlCdpTlvCapabilities
rlCdpTlvCapabilities.description: The Device's Functional Capabilities as will be advertised in subsequent CDP messages. For latest set of specific values, see the latest version of the CDP specification.

rlCdpTlvVersion.name: rlCdpTlvVersion
rlCdpTlvVersion.description: The Version string as will be advertised in subsequent CDP messages.

rlCdpTlvPlatform.name: rlCdpTlvPlatform
rlCdpTlvPlatform.description: The Device's Hardware Platform as will be advertised in subsequent CDP messages.

rlCdpTlvNativeVLAN.name: rlCdpTlvNativeVLAN
rlCdpTlvNativeVLAN.description: The local device's interface's native VLAN, as will be advertised in subsequent CDP messages.

rlCdpTlvDuplex.name: rlCdpTlvDuplex
rlCdpTlvDuplex.description: The local device's interface's duplex mode, as will be advertised in subsequent CDP messages.

rlCdpTlvApplianceID.name: rlCdpTlvApplianceID
rlCdpTlvApplianceID.description: The local device's Appliance ID, as will be advertised in subsequent CDP messages. A value of zero denotes no Appliance VLAN-ID TLV will be advertised in subsequent CDP messages.

rlCdpTlvApplianceVlanID.name: rlCdpTlvApplianceVlanID
rlCdpTlvApplianceVlanID.description: The local device's VoIP VLAN ID, as will be advertised in subsequent CDP messages. A value of zero denotes no Appliance VLAN-ID TLV will be advertised in subsequent CDP messages.

rlCdpTlvExtendedTrust.name: rlCdpTlvExtendedTrust
rlCdpTlvExtendedTrust.description: The local device's interface's extended trust mode, as will be advertised in subsequent CDP messages. A value of zero indicates the absence of extended trust.

rlCdpTlvCosForUntrustedPorts.name: rlCdpTlvCosForUntrustedPorts
rlCdpTlvCosForUntrustedPorts.description: The COS value with which all packets received on an untrusted port should be marked by a simple switching device which cannot itself classify individual packets. This TLV only has any meaning if corresponding instance of rlCdpTlvExtendedTrust indicates the absence of extended trust.

rlCdpTlvPowerAvailableRequestId.name: rlCdpTlvPowerAvailableRequestId
rlCdpTlvPowerAvailableRequestId.description: The Power Available TLV Request-ID field echoes the Request-ID field last received in a Power Requested TLV. It is 0 if no Power Requested TLV has been received since the interface last transitioned to ifOperState == Up.

rlCdpTlvPowerAvailablePowerManagementId.name: rlCdpTlvPowerAvailablePowerManagementId
rlCdpTlvPowerAvailablePowerManagementId.description: The Power Available TLV Power-Management-ID field.

rlCdpTlvPowerAvailable.name: rlCdpTlvPowerAvailable
rlCdpTlvPowerAvailable.description: The Power Available TLV Available-Power field indicates the number of milliwatts of power available to powered devices at the time this object is instatiated.

rlCdpTlvPowerAvailableManagementPowerLev.name: rlCdpTlvPowerAvailableManagementPowerLevel
rlCdpTlvPowerAvailableManagementPowerLev.description: The Power Available TLV Management-Power-Level field indicates the number of milliwatts representing the supplier's request to the powered device for its Power Consumption TLV. A value of 0xFFFFFFFF indicates the local device has no preference.

rlCdpTlvSysName.name: rlCdpTlvSysName
rlCdpTlvSysName.description: The sysName MIB as will be advertised in subsequent CDP messages.

rlCdpAdvertiseApplianceTlv.name: rlCdpAdvertiseApplianceTlv
rlCdpAdvertiseApplianceTlv.description: By setting the MIB to True Appliance VLAN-ID TLV may be advertised. A value of False will prevent this TLV from being advertised.

rlCdpValidateMandatoryTlvs.name: rlCdpValidateMandatoryTlvs
rlCdpValidateMandatoryTlvs.description: By setting the MIB to true all mandatory TLVs 0x0001-0x0006 will be validated. Incoming CDP frames without any of the TLVs will be dropped. A value of false indicates that only the Device ID TLV (0x0001) is mandatory. Frames containing Device ID TLV will be processed, regardless of whether other TLVs are present or not.

rlCdpInterfaceCountersTable.name: rlCdpInterfaceCountersTable
rlCdpInterfaceCountersTable.description: This table contains all CDP counters values, indexed by interface id.

rlCdpInterfaceCountersEntry.name: rlCdpInterfaceCountersEntry
rlCdpInterfaceCountersEntry.description: The row definition for this table.

rlCdpInterfaceId.name: rlCdpInterfaceId
rlCdpInterfaceId.description: Interface id, used as index for interface counters table.

rlCdpInterfaceTotalInputPackets.name: rlCdpInterfaceTotalInputPackets
rlCdpInterfaceTotalInputPackets.description: Num of received packets on rlCdpInterfaceId

rlCdpInterfaceV1InputPackets.name: rlCdpInterfaceV1InputPackets
rlCdpInterfaceV1InputPackets.description: Num of v1 received packets on rlCdpInterfaceId

rlCdpInterfaceV2InputPackets.name: rlCdpInterfaceV2InputPackets
rlCdpInterfaceV2InputPackets.description: Num of v2 received packets on rlCdpInterfaceId

rlCdpInterfaceTotalOutputPackets.name: rlCdpInterfaceTotalOutputPackets
rlCdpInterfaceTotalOutputPackets.description: Num of sent packets from rlCdpInterfaceId

rlCdpInterfaceV1OutputPackets.name: rlCdpInterfaceV1OutputPackets
rlCdpInterfaceV1OutputPackets.description: Num of v1 sent packets from rlCdpInterfaceId

rlCdpInterfaceV2OutputPackets.name: rlCdpInterfaceV2OutputPackets
rlCdpInterfaceV2OutputPackets.description: Num of v2 sent packets from rlCdpInterfaceId

rlCdpInterfaceIllegalChksum.name: rlCdpInterfaceIllegalChksum
rlCdpInterfaceIllegalChksum.description: Num of received packets with illegal CDP checksum.

rlCdpInterfaceErrorPackets.name: rlCdpInterfaceErrorPackets
rlCdpInterfaceErrorPackets.description: specifies the number of received CDP packets with other error (duplicated TLVs, illegal TLVs, etc.)

rlCdpInterfaceMaxNeighborsExceededInMain.name: rlCdpInterfaceMaxNeighborsExceededInMainCache
rlCdpInterfaceMaxNeighborsExceededInMain.description: specifies the number of times a CDP neighbor could not be stored in the main cache.

rlCdpInterfaceMaxNeighborsExceededInSeco.name: rlCdpInterfaceMaxNeighborsExceededInSecondaryCache
rlCdpInterfaceMaxNeighborsExceededInSeco.description: specifies the number of times a CDP neighbor could not be stored in the secondary cache.

rlCdpInterfaceCountersClear.name: rlCdpInterfaceCountersClear
rlCdpInterfaceCountersClear.description: By setting the scalar to a interface id , all error and traffic counters of this interface are set to zero. To clear the counters for ALL interfaces set the scalar to 0x0FFFFFFF

rlCdpLogMismatchDuplexTrap.name: rlCdpLogMismatchDuplexTrap
rlCdpLogMismatchDuplexTrap.description: Warning trap indicating that duplex mismatch has been detected by CDP

rlCdpLogMismatchVoiceVlanTrap.name: rlCdpLogMismatchVoiceVlanTrap
rlCdpLogMismatchVoiceVlanTrap.description: Warning trap indicating that voice vlan mismatch has been detected by CDP

rlCdpLogMismatchNativeVlanTrap.name: rlCdpLogMismatchNativeVlanTrap
rlCdpLogMismatchNativeVlanTrap.description: Warning trap indicating that native vlan mismatch has been detected by CDP
